{% call components.section("Style") -%}

  <p>A tooltip can be placed on a light or dark background. It includes text wrapped in a background container that can sometimes have a drop shadow. The background container also includes an arrow that can point to different icons.</p>

  <div class="margin-top--4">
    {% call components.example(palette='light') %}
      <div class="margin-top--4 centered margin-bottom--4">
        <img src="{{ '/assets/tooltip/tooltip-blueprint.svg' | url }}" alt="Tooltip component style" style="--inline-img-max-width: 324px;">
      </div>
    {%- endcall %}
  </div>

  <h4>Light theme</h4>

  {% call components.example(palette='light') %}
    <img src="{{ '/assets/tooltip/tooltip-theme-light.svg' | url }}" alt="Tooltip component, light theme" style="--example-img-max-width: 272px;">
  {%- endcall %}

  <h4>Dark theme</h4>

  {% call components.example(palette='darkest') %}
    <img src="{{ '/assets/tooltip/tooltip-theme-dark.svg' | url }}" alt="Tooltip component, dark theme" style="--example-img-max-width: 272px;">
  {%- endcall %}

{%- endcall %}

{% call components.section("Usage") -%}

  <h4>Content</h4>

  <p>Content in a tooltip is limited to text only and should be brief and helpful to a user.</p>

  <!-- Temporary Warning alert until web component release -->
  <p style="background-color: #fdf7e7; border-top: 2px solid #f0ab00; padding: 16px 16px 16px 24px; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 0.2px;"><span style="color:#795600"><strong>Warning</strong></span><br />If content needs to be more thorough or interactive elements need to be included, use a <a href="../popover" target="_blank">Popover</a> or <a href="../modal" target="_blank">Modal</a> component instead.</p>

  <h4>Icon pairing</h4>

  <p>A tooltip should always be paired with an icon, link, or other small element.</p>

  <div class="margin-top--4 margin-bottom--4">
    {% call components.example(palette='light') %}
      <img src="{{ '/assets/tooltip/tooltip-icon-pairing.svg' | url }}" alt="Tooltip component icon pairing" style="--inline-img-max-width: 574px;">
    {%- endcall %}
  </div>

  <h4>Orientations</h4>

  <p>A tooltip is available in several orientations depending on the amount of content or available screen space. When choosing an orientation, be mindful of how a tooltip can potentially cover up important content or get cut off by the browser window.</p>

  <div class="margin-top--4 margin-bottom--4">
    {% call components.example(palette='light') %}
      <img src="{{ '/assets/tooltip/tooltip-orientations.svg' | url }}" alt="Tooltip component orientations" style="--inline-img-max-width: 692px;">
    {%- endcall %}
  </div>

{%- endcall %}

{% call components.section("Behavior") -%}

  <p>How a user interacts with a tooltip depends on what size the screen is.</p>

  <ul>
    <li>On large screens, a tooltip disappears after a user moves their cursor away from the icon.</li>
    <li>On large screens, a tooltip disappears after the focus indicator is moved away from the icon.</li>
    <li>On small screens, a tooltip disappears after a user taps the icon again.</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="margin-top--4 margin-bottom--4">
    {% call components.example(palette='light') %}
      <img src="{{ '/assets/tooltip/tooltip-behavior.svg' | url }}" alt="Tooltip component behavior" style="--inline-img-max-width: 516px;">
    {%- endcall %}
  </div>

  {%- endcall %}

  {% call components.section("Responsive design") -%}

  <p>A tooltip can be used on both large and small screens depending on the amount of content or available screen space.</p>

  <h4>Breakpoints</h4>

  <p>A tooltip mostly remains the same on large and small screens.</p>

  <h4>Large screens</h4>

  <div class="margin-top--0 margin-bottom--7">
    <img src="{{ '/assets/tooltip/tooltip-responsive-large-screens.svg' | url }}" alt="Tooltip component responsive design, large screens" style="--inline-img-max-width: 1000px;">
  </div>

  <h4>Small screens</h4>

  <img src="{{ '/assets/tooltip/tooltip-responsive-small-screens.svg' | url }}" alt="Tooltip component responsive design, small screens" style="--inline-img-max-width: 360px;">

{%- endcall %}

{% call components.section("Interaction states") -%}

  <p>A tooltip appears next to an icon on hover, focus, or when tapped.</p>

  <div class="margin-top--4 margin-bottom--4">
    {% call components.example(palette='light') %}
      <img src="{{ '/assets/tooltip/tooltip-interaction-states.svg' | url }}" alt="Tooltip component interaction states, hovered or tapped" style="--inline-img-max-width: 608px;">
    {%- endcall %}
  </div>

  {%- endcall %}

  {% call components.section("Best practices") -%}

  <h4>Accessibility</h4>

  <p>Do not use a dark theme (white) tooltip on a light environment because it will blend into the background too much.</p>

  {% call components.example(palette='wrong') %}
    <div class="inline-flex centered">
      <img src="{{ '/assets/tooltip/tooltip-best-practice-1.svg' | url }}" alt="Tooltip component best practice 1" style="--inline-img-max-width: 264px;">
    </div>
  {%- endcall %}

  <h4>Orientation</h4>

  <p>Content within a tooltip should not be cut off by the browser window. Change the tooltip orientation or break the text into multiple lines if it does.</p>

  {% call components.example(palette='wrong') %}
    <div class="inline-flex centered">
      <img src="{{ '/assets/tooltip/tooltip-best-practice-2.svg' | url }}" alt="Tooltip component best practice 2" style="--inline-img-max-width: 360px;">
    </div>
  {%- endcall %}

  <h4>Pairing</h4>

  <p>Do not add a tooltip to things that do not require further explanation, like obvious links or components.</p>

  {% call components.example(palette='wrong') %}
    <div class="inline-flex centered">
      <img src="{{ '/assets/tooltip/tooltip-best-practice-3.svg' | url }}" alt="Tooltip component best practice 3" style="--inline-img-max-width: 186px;">
    </div>
  {%- endcall %}

{%- endcall %}

{% call components.section("Spacing") -%}

  <p>A Tooltip uses <a href="https://www.patternfly.org/v4/guidelines/spacers">PatternFly 4 spacers</a> to define spacing values between elements. Every tooltip orientation contains the same amount padding in between the arrow and icon.</p>

  {% call components.example(palette='light') %}
    <img src="{{ '/assets/tooltip/tooltip-spacing-theme-light.svg' | url }}" alt="Tooltip component spacing, light theme" style="--example-img-max-width: 280px;">
  {%- endcall %}

{%- endcall %}

